Unit Overview

This unit applied quantitative models to real-world problems, including social engineering threat analysis.

Artefacts

Attack tree and Markov model notes

Seminar workshop answers

Individual Contribution

I analysed how quantitative models support decision-making in security contexts.

Reflection

Implementing models revealed the importance of aligning mathematical outputs with business impact. Quantitative risk models are most valuable when they support prioritisation and policy decisions rather than acting as purely academic exercises.

